{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<u>'''The First One'''</u>|final='''<u>The Beginning</u>|body=
<br>''When I see the colors of them, I feel...calm. I feel like the flowers are calling me, inviting me to feel happy again. I see miles and miles of beautiful lavender flowers, all glowing its shining color onto me. The brightness gives me a sense of calm, a peace I have not felt in years. I... I never want to leave this place. I never want to wake up.}}''

==<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> Description </span>==

Level 175 takes place in a field of lavender flowers. The level's expanse is unknown and thought to be limitless. The level is all in the wanderer's mind, and until they wake up, they will remain stuck in the level. When they enter the level, they will have nothing with them but the clothes they were wearing when they were sleeping. Despite being in their own minds, they cannot conjure anything within their own thoughts and are limited to the resources in the levels. Moreover, they will still have hunger and thirst and therefore must eat and hydrate. The only place to find food and water is in the medieval-styled houses in the level.

{{Blurimage|file=The Castle House.jpg|caption=Staged photograph outside of level 175 showing a copy of the medieval house looks like.|align=right}}
While mostly fields of lavender flowers, there are houses that have an outward look of a medieval house made out of stone. Despite that, the inside of the houses are very different in contrast to the outside. The houses are very modern with many comfortable amenities provided to the wanderer. The house has food and drinks provided to the wanderer, with a rare chance of the wanderer's familiar food they love being among them. These houses, however, will disappear within three hours when entered, alongside any food and drinks in them.

The houses, both fake and real, are very rare to find. With both being confirmed that one must walk 40 miles just to find one. This includes fake houses, which also spawn in the level. These fake houses spawn more regularly than the actual houses themselves. The fake houses just have an outside and can't be opened. The odds of finding the real houses are 1 in 4, so it takes 8 hours to an entire day to find one.

==<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> Entities </span>==

{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<u>'''The First Trap'''</u>|final='''<u>A man's pleasure is his undoing.</u>|body=
<br>''It is like god himself created this field, and the lavender colors are his eyes. I cannot help but feel pure bliss when I look to the skies and see the beauties of the skies...but it does give me pause. I must ask through...why am I here? What am I doing in these fields. ...I fell asleep and woke up here. I am grateful, but I do need to get back sometime. ...How do I get out of here?}}''

===<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> The Lavender Flowers </span>===

The lavender flowers that cover most of the level are each an entity. Whenever one walks over the flowers, they will not be crushed. Whenever one does walk over them shortly after, they will instead grow slightly taller. This will only happen during the day, as this effect does not persist at night. Whenever one walks over the flowers instead of the dirt paths, they will experience more joyful emotions than usual. Like the flower growing, this effect does not work at night.

{{Blurimage|file=Lavender Dream.png|caption=Staged photograph outside of level 175 showing a replica of the lavender fields. |align=right}}
If one stays for more than an hour in the lavender fields, it is said that they will hear voices coming from the flowers. These voices have various sayings, but they encourage wanderers to stay in the fields and relax. And if one is heading towards the dirt path, they will discourage wanderers from going on the paths, saying that they will be sad. If one does go back to the paths, however, the voices will stop.

If one picks a lavender flower from the field, they will feel a mild sting on their forehead. If one picks the flower while the voices are active, the voices will get angry and insult the wanderer for around two minutes straight. If one puts the flower down, the ground will immediately swallow it up, and it will pop up in the exact spot one dropped it on.

==<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> The Violet Virus </span>==

{{Collapse|num=3|initial=<u>'''The First Victim'''</u>|final='''<u>He starts to see for what this all is.</u>|body=
<br>''Something is wrong, really wrong. My vision is getting worse and worse by the hours and my skin is... turning purple. I've never seen something like this before, and I'm damn sure It's nothing good. It's on my legs and right arm, been running rampant the last 7 or 8 hours. I need help, but I'm not sure I can make it.  ...I'm dying soon, aren't I?''}}

The Violet Virus is an infectious disease that starts to spread throughout the wanderer's physical body that lies asleep while they are inside their own minds in the lavender fields. The level is in their own minds, a mental trap from the virus. As soon as one falls asleep, the infection will start on their sleeping bodies. In their minds, however, they will be mentally convinced they are on an entirely new level, unaware of even being asleep, let alone their real physical bodies being infected. They will forget where they were and what supplies they had on them, and if they had any goals or objectives to complete, they will completely forget that task unless they manage to wake.

When wanderers first fall asleep upon getting the virus, there will be no signs they even have it until 8-9 hours in. At 8-9 hours, their real sleeping bodies will start sweating all over, and their foreheads will start reaching temperatures of around 100 degrees Fahrenheit (38 degrees Celsius). At around the 12-hour mark, the rest of the body will turn to that same temperature. It is also at this point the real body will start to have a lavender scent, so other people will recognize it is the Violet Virus.

{{Blurimage|file=Lavender Fields.jpg|caption=Staged photograph outside of level 175 showing a replica of the lavender fields with skies slowly turning lavender. |align=right}}
Around 24 hours into getting the virus is when it will start to turn the real body a lavender color, starting with the hands. At the 36-hour mark, both the real body's hands and feet will be fully lavender, with the lavender color also up the elbows and knees of the real body, and the lavender scent will become even more prevalent. It is also at this point where the flowers will stop talking in the wanderer's mind.

After around 48 hours, the entire lower half of the wanderer's real body will be a lavender color, and purple dots will start appearing all over the purple half of the real body. Inside the wanderer's mind, they will start having doubts. Their vision will start becoming clearer and will start to remember where they were before, what their objectives/goals were before coming here, etc.

Around 60 hours in, their entire real body will be a lavender color except for their face. Inside the mind, they will start to panic, frantically looking for an exit. The sky inside their own minds will turn purple, and the castles will disappear, and a wind will start to pick up in their minds. 

Around 72 hours in, the real body of the wanderer will turn fully lavender. In the mind, the wanderer will fully remember everything about themselves. The winds will intensify, and the lavender flowers will start to turn to dust. After another hour they will wake from their minds and back into their real body, but it is too late.

Just an hour after waking, the wanderer will start to experience a burning sensation, and lavender dots will start to rapidly pop up around their already lavender body. Despite being in their real body, the flower voices will return. It is around this point that organs will start to fail and, after 73 hours, finally succumb to the virus.

===<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> The Morado Man </span>===

{{Collapse|num=4|initial=<u>'''The First Fatality'''</u>|final='''<u>Once he appears, there is no hope.</u>|body=
<br>''I...I feel him watching me. He was over there, but I haven't seen him for a good 30 minutes now. He...he just stares at me, yet I feel like my life is in danger. Is he the warning? Is he death? In truth I could never figure it out. I just have one goal, to get out of whatever this place is. ...I hope to not see him again, but if I know anything about this place...I will.''}}

The Morado Man is a mysterious entity that appears 48 hours after the infection has started. He appears as an entirely lavender man with no distinguishing features asides from huge eyes. He wears an exact copy of whatever the wanderer is wearing, and even copies any physical deformities if the wanderer has any. When he is near the flowers, there will be voices that scream, begging for the wanderer to run.

Despite the flowers warning the wanderer to run, he will not chase them. But he will teleport around them from a distance. He will keep an eye on the wanderer for unknown durations. The duration when he watches them can last from a couple of minutes to many hours. The wanderer will know they are being watched by him when they get a feeling of dread.

When the wanderer wakes up from their fake body into the real body, they will stop seeing the Morado Man for most of the final hour they are alive. From when they wake up until five minutes before dying, they will not see him. When they do however, they will see him initially from far away and feel dread. The Morado Man will have the same eyes but will also now have a mouth with yellow spike teeth. He will slowly walk to the wanderer, with the sense of dread increasing as he gets closer until they are just inches from the wanderer until they finally pass on, unable to speak.



==<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> Groups and Orginizations </span>==

Due to the level taking place in the mind, it is not possible to set up any sort of bases. Outside of the level, there is a group dedicated to stopping the virus and developing a vaccine for it. Known as the V.E.G (Violet Extermination Group), they are a team of 23 scientists and medical experts researching day and night for any possible leads to combat the Violet Virus. They have successfully managed to create pills that can delay getting the virus, but it has only been proven to be effective for people who entered level 778.



==<span style="font-family:Distressed Typewriter; color: #ece8ff; text-shadow: 3px 1px 0 #c912c0, 5px 9px 5px #a64ea1"> Entrance </span>==

It is not known how one gets the virus, as it starts to infect when one is asleep. There is an anomaly, as people who have been in levels with more purple colors than most have the most chance of contracting the virus. The most amount of people who have gotten the virus have mainly been to either [[Level 870]], [[Level 778]], and [[Level 660]]. 

